previous.name: Haakaa Supplemental Feeding Combo Grey
previous.description:
Information

Haakaa's Silicone Feeding Tube and Generation 3 Baby Bottle now come together as a convenient Supplemental Feeding Combo for mothers who are experiencing feeding or latching issues with their babies. If you and your baby experience feeding issues – including latching problems, low milk supply, or maybe little ones that need a little extra nourishment or help to learn how to feed – then the Silicone Feeding Tube Set could be of assistance to you. It helps you to overcome some of these common issues by connecting a bottle of supplemented milk to your breast via a tube, delivering a constant and controllable flow of milk to baby at the breast.

It includes:
1 x Silicone Feeding Tube Set
1 x 250ml Gen. 3 Silicone Baby Bottle with an X-shaped Variable Flow Nipple.

The benefits of this feeding tube set are:

  • Feeding tube made with food grade silicone and polyformaldehyde.Flow controller provides a consistent flow of liquid.Provides added nutrition to the baby, while also giving mum and baby the sensation of breastfeeding.
  • Long and slim tube for inconspicuous and discreet use. Baby bottle made of food grade silicone with great anti-impact performance. Soft, naturally-shaped silicone nipple designed to closely mimic breastfeeding.
  • Multifunctional design, compatible with Gen. 3 attachments. Ultra-wide neck design allows for easy cleaning. Safe in microwaves, boiling water and sterilisers. BPA, PVC and phthalate-free.

Ingredients

100% food grade silicone

How To Use

1. Insert both the inlet and outlet tubes into ends of the tube adapter. Thread the end of the outlet tube through the flow controller.
2. Push the thick inlet tube down through the X-shaped opening on the Variable Flow Nipple and pull it through until it is long enough to reach the milk in the bottle. Attach the nipple to the bottle.
3. Place the end of the thin outlet tube 1-2cm away from your nipple and secure its position with medical tape.
4. Introduce your baby to your nipple and then place the thin outlet tube gently into their mouth to begin feeding.
5. Squeeze the Gen. 3 Silicone Baby Bottle body to control the flow of milk. Increase pressure on the bottle to increase the speed that milk flows or reduce pressure to slow it down. You can also use the flow controller to manager the speed that milk flows, adjusting to suit your child.

Top Tip: The Haakaa Supplemental Silicone Feeding Tube Set can be used with any baby bottle, as long as it is fitted with an X-shaped variable flow teat. Simply place the bottle above the end of the tube that is taped to your breast and let gravity do the work as your milk flows through the tube.

Warnings

Check product condition before each use. Immediately discontinue use and replace if these products shows any signs of damage. Do not store near any sharp objects. While the Silicone Feeding Tube may be compatible with other X-shaped teats, we recommend only using this product with a Haakaa Gen. 3 Variable Flow Nipple. Smaller teats may tear when inserting the tube. Only soft bristle brushes or soft sponges should be used to clean these products, as hard scourers may scratch the surface. Exposure to detergent may make the silicone in these products appear cloudy. These products are not toys. Do not use these products for anything other than their intended use. Store products in a cool, dry place and avoid direct sunlight. Adult supervision is required.

Note: We recommend visiting a breastfeeding or medical specialist if you have any concerns with breastfeeding and feel this product could be of assistance to you and your baby.

Clean after each use. Use the included cleaning brush to scrub the inside of the tube before rinsing with hot water. For smoother operation, feed the brush through the tube by the handle and pull through. We strongly recommend cleaning and sterilising these products with any steam sterilising system, or by boiling in water for 2-3 minutes. Do not use any bleach-based agents or sterilising tablets to clean these products. Instead, we recommend using the Haakaa Dish Soap. Do not use a UV steriliser to clean these products as it may impact their lifespan.

Naturobest Preconception Multi for Women is a premium multivitamin, multimineral, and antioxidant. This vegan-friendly daily multivitamin is designed to enhance preconception health and prepare the body for a flourishing pregnancy. NaturoBest’s product is Australia’s first preconception multi with Quatrefolic®, the 4th generation folate and folinic acid, ideal for those who have genetic difficulties with metabolising folic acid. Preconception Multi for Women also contains 24mg of elemental iron as Ferrochel® in a daily dose of highly bioavailable iron bisglycinate.

The benefits of these capsules are:

  • Healthy fetal development.
  • Thyroid function and energy levels.
  • Glucose and carbohydrate metabolism.
  • Skin and immune system.

How To Use

Take two capsules daily with food or as directed by your healthcare practitioner. Take one capsule with breakfast and one capsule with lunch. It’s advisable to begin taking preconception vitamins for women at least 3 months before you try to conceive to allow them time to do their work and create the best conditions for healthy conception.

Warnings

Vitamin supplements should not replace a balanced diet. This product contains selenium which is toxic in high doses. A daily dose of 150 micrograms for adults of selenium from dietary supplements should not be exceeded. Not for the treatment of iron deficiency conditions. Always read the label, use only as directed, and if symptoms persist see your healthcare professional. If you have had a baby with a neural tube defect/spina bifida, seek specific medical advice. Store below 25 degrees Celcius in a cool, dry place. Use only if the cap seal is unbroken.

Ingredients

Ferr phos (Ferrum phosphate)
Kali sulph (Potassium sulphate)
Mag phos (Magnesium phosphate)

How to Use

Adults: 1 tablet
Children: 1/2 tablet
Infants: 1/4 tablet

Acute conditions: every half an hour (up to 6 doses per day) until symptoms subside.

Chronic or maintenance dose: 4 times daily.
Take half an hour before meals, last dose at bedtime, or as professionally prescribed

Warnings

Always read the label and use only as directed. If symptoms persist consult your healthcare practitioner. Contains lactose.

previous.description:
Information

In Essence Waterless Pure Essential Oil Diffuser allows users to experience the purity and uncompromised quality of In Essence Pure Essential Oils straight from the source, directly from the bottle. Unlike conventional diffusers, the Waterless Essential Oil Diffuser adopts the latest nebulizing technology to release a fine cool mist composed entirely of pure essential oils, resulting in a much stronger, high potency aroma dispersed throughout the air without the need for heat or water.

The benefits of this waterless diffuser are:

  • Calms the mind, promotes sleep, and uplifts the mind and body.
  • Cordless and compact.
  • Battery-operated unit making it more convenient to experience the benefits of aromatherapy in many places!

How To Use

1. Remove the nozzle by pushing upright through the hole in the base of the diffuser. Attach your In Essence Pure Essential Oil into the nozzle (bottles sizes up to 20mL Compatible). Secure nozzle back into the diffuser, ensuring the marked arrows are aligned (avoid chemical, synthetic oils as these will cause the diffuser to malfunction).

2. Hold the POWER button to turn on the diffuser. This will activate Intermittent mist dispersion. Intermittent mist intervals can be adjusted by further pressing the power button. 1st Press: On 10sec, Off 60sec, Repeat. 2nd Press: On 20sec, Off 60sec, Repeat. 3rd Press: On 30sec, Off 60sec, Repeat.

3. Press TIMER to activate the timer mode (30/60/90 mins). To turn off the diffuser at any time, hold the POWER button.

NOTE: Compatible with essential oil bottles no larger than 20mL. Not all essential oil bottles may be suitable. For full instructions refer to the manual enclosed.

Warnings

Responsible use of Essential Oils Adults Only. Not to be taken. Keep out of reach of children

previous.name: KISS ImPRESS Colour Press-On Manicure - Baby Why So Blue
previous.description:
Information

The Kiss imPRESS Colour Press-On Manicure in Baby Why So Blue is a polish free mani in minutes. Now in Solid Colors-No glue, no bling! Super slim & super comfortable, looks & feels like your own nails. The false nails come ready to wear, no polish required and no drying time! Kit contains 30 Nails, Prep Pad, Mini File, and Wood Stick.

The benefits of these nails are:

  • Natural look and feel
  • Super Hold adhesive
  • No glue needed, safe on natural nails & hassle free removal!
  • Chip proof, smudge proof & no dry time!
  • Includes 30 nails, prep pad, file, wood stick

Ingredients

ABS Plastic. Adhesive: Acrylic Acid, Ethylhexyl Acrylate, Hydroxycyclohexyl Phenyl Ketone Prep pad: Isopropyl Alcohol, Water. Keep out of reach of children. Contains flammable Prep Pad. Wear beyond 7 days is not recommended

How To Use

Size: Prior to application, align nails with tab sides facing your cuticles and find correct size for each nail (jot down the # found on the tab on each nail–1 is largest, 11 is smallest–for future use.) When you are in between sizes go smaller, not larger.
Prep: Wash hands with soap and water and dry thoroughly. Use included cuticle stick to push back any excess skin. Wipe nails with the enclosed prep pad (the most important step), to clean nails for better adhesion. (You can use rubbing alcohol in place of or in addition to prep pad.)
Apply: Peel backing from nail then press it down on your natural nail, in the center and at both sides at the same time. Hold for 30 seconds. (Press on thumbnails last.)
If there is exposed adhesive, brush clear nail polish between your nail and the imPRESS and press down.
Wait at least an hour to wet hands or file nails if desired.

The Kiss ImPRESS Colour Press-On Manicure in Paralyzed Pink is a polish free mani in minutes. Now in Solid Colors-No glue, no bling! Super slim & super comfortable, looks & feels like your own nails.
The false nails come ready to wear, no polish required and no drying time! Kit contains 30 Nails, Prep Pad, Mini File, and Wood Stick.

The benefits of these nails are:

  • Natural look and feel
  • Super Hold adhesive
  • No glue needed, safe on natural nails & hassle free removal!
  • Chip proof, smudge proof & no dry time!
  • Includes 30 nails, prep pad, file, wood stick

Ingredients

ABS Plastic. Adhesive: Acrylic Acid, Ethylhexyl Acrylate, Hydroxycyclohexyl Phenyl Ketone Prep pad: Isopropyl Alcohol, Water.

How To Use

Size: Prior to application, align nails with tab sides facing your cuticles and find correct size for each nail (jot down the # found on the tab on each nail–1 is largest, 11 is smallest–for future use.) When you are in between sizes go smaller, not larger.
Prep: Wash hands with soap and water and dry thoroughly. Use included cuticle stick to push back any excess skin. Wipe nails with the enclosed prep pad (the most important step), to clean nails for better adhesion. (You can use rubbing alcohol in place of or in addition to prep pad.)
Apply: Peel backing from nail then press it down on your natural nail, in the center and at both sides at the same time. Hold for 30 seconds. (Press on thumbnails last.)
If there is exposed adhesive, brush clear nail polish between your nail and the imPRESS and press down.
Wait at least an hour to wet hands or file nails if desired.

Warnings

Keep out of reach of children. Contains flammable Prep Pad. Wear beyond 7 days is not recommended

previous.name: Robitussin Dry Cough Forte Oral Liquid 200ml - Cherry Vanilla
previous.description:
Information

Robitussin has throat soothing formula that controls coughs for up to 8 hours. It provides symptomatic relief of dry, irritating and hacking coughs. Robitussin Dry Cough Forte provides long lasting relief for up to 8 hours in adults and children from dry, irritating and hacking coughs. Robitussin liquid coats and soothes the throat. Contains the cough suppressant Dextromethorphan hydrobromide monohydrate to relieve coughs due to minor throat and bronchial irritations as may occur with a cold.

Ingredients

Active Ingredient: Dextromethorphan hydrobromide Monohydrate 15mg/5mL. Contains Benzoates, Hydroxybenzoates, Saccharin, Sulfites, Sugars.

How To Use

Every 6 to 8 hours orally when necessary. Adults and Children 12 years and over: 10mL Children 6 years - under 12 years: 5mL Do not exceed 4 doses in a 24 hour period. Use in children aged 6 to 11 years only on the advice of a doctor, pharmacist or nurse practitioner.

Warnings

Keep out of reach of children. Do not use this product: - If you are hypersensitive to any of the ingredients - If you are taking prescription medication for depression, psychiatric or emotional conditions e.g. monoamine oxidase inhibitors (MAOI), selective serotonin reuptake inhibitor (SSRI) or Parkinson's disease, or for 2 weeks after stopping the medication. If you are not sure if your prescription medication contains one of these drugs, ask a doctor or pharmacist before taking this product - During an acute asthma attack - In children under 6 years of age Ask your doctor before use if you: - Have a persistent or chronic cough such as occurs with: - smoking - asthma - chronic bronchitis - emphysema - Have a cough with excessive phlegm - Are pregnant or breastfeeding - Are taking other cough and cold medicines While using this product: - Do not exceed the recommended dosage. - Stop use and consult your doctor if you have a cough that persists for more than 1 week, tends to recur or is accompanied by fever, rash or persistent headache. These could be signs of a serious condition. - In case of overdose, stop use and immediately contact the Poisons Information Centre (Australia 13 11 26, New Zealand 0800 764 766) for advice. Do not use if tamper evident cap seal is broken or missing. Store below 25°C.

previous.description:
Information

Gaviscon Dual Action Heartburn & Indigestion Relief brings fast, soothing and long lasting relief from the pain and discomfort of heartburn (gastric reflux) and indigestion. It works in two different ways: 1. More effective reduction of excess stomach acid to relieve discomfort, 2. Forming a protective layer over the stomach contents to soothe the burning pain in your chest.

The benefits of these chewable tablets are:

  • Dual-acting formula for heartburn and indigestion.
  • Convenient relief on the go.
  • Mixed berry flavour.

Ingredients

Per tablet: Sodium Alginate 250mg Sodium Bicarbonate 106.5mg Calcium Carbonate 187.5mg. Contains phenylalanine, mannitol, aspartame, sulphites and sodium.

How To Use

Adults & children over 12 years: 4 tablets. Children 6-12 years: 2 tablets. Take as required after meals and before going to bed, up to 4 times a day or as directed. Chew tablets thoroughly before swallowing and follow with water if desired. Ensure blister pack is unbroken before first use.

Warnings

This medicine may not be right for you. Read the label before purchase. Do not use after expiry date shown. - If symptoms persist see your doctor. - Keep out of reach of children. - Not recommended for children under 6 years. - The maximum total daily intake (16 tablets) for adults contains 894mg of sodium (take into account if on a low sodium diet) and 9.6g mannitol and 4.6g of xylitol. - Products containing mannitol & xylitol may have a laxative effect or cause diarrhoea. - Contains phenylalanine, mannitol, aspartame, sulphites and sodium. Store below 30ºC in a dry place.

previous.name: Louvelle RIVA Hair Towel Wrap - Monochrome Stripe
previous.description:
Information

Louvelle RIVA Hair Towel Wrap gives you the perfect balance between a faster dry and giving your crowning glory the TLC it deserves. When our hair is wet, it is at its most fragile. Rubbing and heat styling your luscious locks in this delicate state can lead to damage, friction and frizz. Created from luxurious yet lightweight and extremely absorbent microfibre, these fashion-forward wrap-style towels can dry your hair in half the time it would take with a regular towel, and hold almost 5x their own weight in water. Unlike some hair towels, the Riva is generously sized, ensuring it truly is a one-size-fits-all affair, while the button closure stays put with ease.

The benefits of this towel wrap are:

  • Protects hair against friction and heat damage.
  • Button closure for easy application.
  • Keeps hair off your face and your hands free to apply makeup.
  • Suitable for all hair types including curly, frizzy, thick, fine, damaged and thinning.

How To Use

Start by gently squeezing out excess water, then flip your hair over. Position the button on your Riva wrap at the nape of your neck and the loop at the front of your head, then wrap it around. Secure at the back of your head with the button.

Care Instructions- Machine wash in delicates bag or hand wash. Line dry (do not tumble dry). Do not use fabric softener which can affect towel absorbency.

previous.name: Louvelle Shower Cap - AMELIE Black
previous.description:
Information

Louvelle Shower Cap is carefully crafted from luxuriously soft and stretchy premium fabric with a waterproof lining, it's original and patented turban-style designs elevate the shower cap from a passé necessity to an everyday luxury. Every bathing beauty knows showers can leave your luscious locks prone to frizz causing humidity. But freshening up doesn’t have to spell the end of your beautiful blow-dry, or leave you compromising on your impeccable style. Streamlined Amelie features a sleek panelled design, while Dahlia’s adjustable knotted style is more voluminous. For larger heads or very long hair we recommend Dahlia over Amelie.

The benefits of this shower cap are:

  • Double layer humidity defying fabric with waterproof lining.
  • Less washing means longer lasting hair colour, less heat styling and healthier hair.
  • Keeps your locks out of your skincare treatments.
  • Long-lasting construction to reduce waste (all those plastic hotel shower caps going to landfill!

How To Use

Gather your luscious locks into a low bun at the base of your head; this fits hair under the cap better than a top knot. Put your Louvelle shower cap on from front to back, just as you would a traditional cap. Adjust as necessary, ensuring all hair is enclosed under your cap.

Care Instructions- Machine wash in delicates bag or hand wash. Line dry (do not tumble dry).

previous.name: Scholl Scholl Ladies Flight Compression Hosiery Socks Natural Size 8-10 1 Pair
previous.description:
Information

Scholl's Ladies Flight Compression Hosiery Socks Natural Size 8-10 (1 Pair) are medically proven to help prevent Deep Vein Thrombosis by helping to improve blood circulation. They also help to prevent swollen ankles and tired aching legs.

The benefits of these socks are:

  • Advanced Hosiery Technology.
  • 30 Denier Semi - Sheer.
  • Ultra - Soft.
  • Comfort top.
  • Reinforced toe.
  • With antimicrobial protection to keep feet fresh.

How To Use

Scholl Flight Socks Ladies should be worn in place of normal hosiery throughout the journey. Always wear both knee high and ensure that they are pulled up to just below the knee. See enclosed leaflet for correct fitting and care. Please keep packaging and leaflet for future reference. Handwash. Do not iron.

Warnings

Do not use if you have serious circulatory problems such as active arterial or venous disease. Please consult a Healthcare Professional on the suitability of this product if you have any of the following: previous history of venous thrombosis (blood clots), superficial vein thrombosis, diabetes, severe obesity, reduced mobility including paralysed lower limb, heart disease, severe varicose veins, recent major surgery or injury to lower limbs/abdomen, stroke, cancer, chemotherapy treatment, genetic blood clotting disorder (eg: Factor V Leiden), or if you are pregnant.

previous.name: Louvelle Riva Hair Towel Wrap - Denim Leopard
previous.description:
Information

Louvelle Riva Hair Towel Wrap is the perfect balance between a faster dry and giving your crowning glory the TLC it deserves. When our hair is wet, it is at its most fragile. Rubbing and heat styling your luscious locks in this delicate state can lead to damage, friction and frizz. Created from luxurious yet lightweight and extremely absorbent microfibre, these fashion-forward wrap-style towels can dry your hair in half the time it would take with a regular towel, and hold almost 5x their own weight in water. Unlike some hair towels, the Riva is generously sized, ensuring it truly is a one-size-fits-all affair, while the button closure stays put with ease.

The benefits of this hair towel are:

  • Minimises frizz.
  • Reduces blow dry time.
  • Button closure for easy application.
  • Keeps hair off your face and your hands free to apply makeup.
  • Suitable for all hair types including curly, frizzy, thick, fine, damaged and thinning.

How To Use

The Riva hair towel is just as easy to wear as a regular towel! Start by gently squeezing out excess water, then flip your hair over. Position the button on your Riva wrap at the nape of your neck and the loop at the front of your head, then wrap it around. Secure at the back of your head with the button.

Care: Machine wash in delicates bag or hand wash. Line dry (do not tumble dry). Do not use fabric softener which can affect towel absorbency.

previous.description:
Information

Aspro Tablets provide fast & effective temporary relief from: headaches, sore throat, toothaches, rheumatic and arthritic pain, pain associated with cold & flu symptoms, inflammation associated with muscular aches and pains, neuralgia, fibrositis and period pain. Also reduces fever.

The benefits of these tablets are:

  • Soluble effervescent tablets.
  • Fast, effective temporary relief from pain.
  • Starts to work fast because it forms a clear solution once dissolved, ready to be absorbed as soon as you drink it.

Ingredients

Each Tablet contains Aspirin 300mg.

How To Use

Adults: Take 2-3 tablets dissolved in half a glass of water every 4 hours as necessary. Children over 12 years: Take 1-2 tablets dissolved in half a glass of water every 4 hours as necessary. Do not exceed 12 tablets in 24hrs unless directed by a doctor.

Warnings

Always read the label. Contains sulfites and sorbates. Follow the directions for use. If symptoms persist, talk to your health professional. Incorrect use could be harmful. Do not use if you have a stomach ulcer, heart failure, are pregnant or allergic to anti-inflammatory medicines. Do not use this product : - if you have a stomach ulcer or history of heart failure - during the first 6 months of pregnancy unless advised by a doctor. Do not use at all in the last 3 months of pregnancy - if you are allergic to aspirin or other anti-inflammatory medicines. - if you get an allergic reaction, stop taking and see your doctor immediately. - if you are taking anticoagulant therapy Unless a doctor has told you to, do not use this product: - for more than a few days at a time - in children under 12 years of age - in children 12-16 years of age with or recovering from chicken pox, influenza or fever. - if you have asthma - with other medicines containing aspirin or anti-inflammatory medicines that you are taking regularly - if you have impaired kidney or liver function See a doctor before taking for thinning the blood or for your heart. Contains saccharin sodium, sulfites and sorbates. Each tablet contains 161mg of sodium. Store below 25°C. Protect from moisture.

previous.name: Luvin Life pH Strips For Saliva And Urine 100 Strips
previous.description:
Information

Luvin Life pH Strips For Saliva And Urine are easy to use strips that test the pH levels in your saliva or in your urine. Have you been feeling off- Colour? Suffering from headaches, insomnia and lack of energy? These are just some of the symptoms you may experience if your body's PH balance is out of balance. Too much acidity can also cause depression, frequent infections, sensitive teeth, gastritis, brittle nails, dry skin, leg cramps, and those annoying little ulcers on your tongue. The ideal pH level for our bodies is around 7.0 to 7.4 but, due to the acidic food we eat nowadays, and stress, many of us are falling way below that.

The benefits of these strips are:

  • Super sensitive.
  • 15-second results.
  • Track your pH throughout the day.
  • Easy to read 2 Colour panel.
  • Wide RangepH 4.5 pH 9.0.
  • 100 strips.
  • Sterile and sealed for freshness.

How To Use

Dip the strip into saliva or urine & read after 15 seconds.

To test urine: Test the first and second urine of the day and record the average reading. To test, briefly place pH strip into the urine stream, shake the excess fluid and wait 15 seconds to read your pH.

To test saliva: Wait two hours after eating. Spit saliva into a spoon, dip the pH strip into the fluid and wait 15 seconds to read your pH.

Results: A reading of 7.0+ is acidic and below 6.0 is very acidic. Test 2-3 times per day at first then daily once pH balance is optimised to the optimal range. Danger pH level4.5 5.75 or 7.5 9.0, Concern for pH level6.0 6.5, Optimal pH level6.75 7.4

previous.name: Bellamy's Organic Junior Milk Drink Step 4 900ml
previous.description:
Information

Bellamy's Organic Junior Milk Drink Step 4 is a premium nutrient dense milk drink, carefully crafted to support active young children over 3 years of age, when dietary intake may be inadequate. An enriched alternative to ordinary cow’s milk, Bellamy's Organic Junior Milk Drink is made from certified organic cow’s milk, fortified with omega-3 DHA, prebiotics (GOS & FOS) and 16 essential vitamins and minerals for growth and development.

The benefits of this formula are:

  • Iron, Iodine & Zinc for healthy cognitive function.
  • Folate, Vitamins B6, B12, C & D for a healthy immune system.
  • Calcium, Magnesium & Vitamin D for strong teeth & bone structure.
  • Vitamin A essential for normal vision.
  • No added sucrose & no flavours, colours or preservatives.

Ingredients

Organic milk solids [organic whole milk liquid or powder, organic skim milk liquid or powder, organic demineralised whey powder, organic lactose powder], organic vegetable oil [organic soybean oil, organic sunflower oil, emulsifier (organic soybean lecithin)], organic galacto-oligosaccharides liquid (GOS) from milk, organic fructo-oligosaccharides liquid powder (FOS), dried DHA [fish oil (tuna), sodium caseinate, emulsifier (soybean lecithin), antioxidants (sodium ascorbate, mixed tocopherols, ascorbyl palmitate)]. Minerals: Calcium phosphate, calcium carbonate, magnesium carbonate, ferrous sulphate, zinc sulphate, potassium iodide, magnesium chloride. Vitamins: Sodium ascorbate, vitamin E acetate, vitamin A acetate, niacinamide, vitamin D3, thiamine hydrochloride, pyridoxine hydrochloride, folic acid, vitamin B12. Allergens: Contains milk, fish & soy.

How To Use

Please follow feeding table. 1 scoop = 8.8 g of powder. The Feeding Table is only a general guide. Your baby may need more or less than indicated.

1. Always wash hands before preparing. Wash and rinse cup or bottle and all utensils thoroughly. Use only the enclosed scoop.

2. Fill the measuring scoop with powder and level off using the levelling blade on the tin. Always add one level scoop (8.6 g) of powder to each 50 mL of drinking water.

3. Add 4 level scoops (34.4 g) of Organic Junior Milk Drink to 200 mL of drinking water.

4. Whisk, shake or stir the mixture briskly until powder dissolves and serve immediately. If prepared milk drink is not consumed immediately refrigerate and use within 24 hours.

previous.description:
Information

LittleOak Natural Goat Milk Follow-On Formula 2 is designed for 6-12 months, and is made from fresh whole goat’s milk straight from New Zealand. Starting with fresh milk means less processing, more natural goodness. Goat’s milk is a delicious, creamy alternative to cow’s milk. LittleOak Infant Formula is nutritionally complete and proudly manufactured locally to the highest food safety standards, using only non-GMO ingredients.

The benefits of this formula are:

  • Designed for infants 6-12 months.
  • First certified palm oil free formula in the world.
  • Made from the goodness of fresh whole goat’s milk.

Ingredients

Full Cream Goat Milk Solids, Lactose, LittleOak Proprietary Oil Blend (Sunflower Oil, High Oleic Sunflower Oil, Pressed Coconut Oil, Pressed Flaxseed Oil), Galacto-oligosaccharide (GOS), Minerals (Tricalcium Phosphate, Calcium Citrate, Trisodium Citrate, Magnesium Sulphate, Ferrous Lactate, Zinc Sulphate, Sodium Selenite, Copper Gluconate, Manganese Sulphate, Potassium Iodide), DHA Powder (Docosahexaenoic Oil from Schizochytrium sp.), ARA Powder (Arachidonic Acid Oil from Mortierella alpine), L-Tyrosine, Choline Chloride, Vitamins (Sodium Ascorbate, Vitamin E Acetate, Vitamin A Acetate, Niacinamide, Vitamin D3, Calcium Pantothenate, Vitamin B12, Vitamin K1, Thiamin Hydrochloride, Pyridoxine Hydrochloride, Riboflavin, Folic Acid, Biotin), Inositol, L-Cysteine, L-Tryptophan, Antioxidant (α-Tocopherol), L-Carnitine. Allergens: Contains milk. Made using Goat Milk Protein.

How To Use

All LittleOak formula tins will provide you with the necessary measuring scoop and preparation instructions, along with a feeding table to guide you on how much your baby will need each day. Follow instructions exactly. Prepare bottles, teats, and water as directed. Do not change the proportions of powder except on medical advice.

1. Wash hands before preparing LittleOak Infant Formula. Sterilise all utensils for 5 minutes or using an approved steriliser.

2. Only use the enclosed LittleOak scoop. Fill the scoop and level off using the provided leveller. Avoid compacting powder.

3. Always add one level scoop of powder for each 50mL of water. Mix thoroughly by shaking gently or swirling the bottle to dissolve the powder.

4. Test temperature on wrist before use. It should feel lukewarm, not hot. If it feels too hot, cool down by holding the bottle under cold water. Be sure none of this water gets into the feed. Feed immediately.

5. Discard any unfinished milk. Each bottle should be prepared individually. If the bottle is prepared for storage prior to use, ensure it is refrigerated and used within 24 hours.

The peri bottle is used for rinsing your perineum with warm water after you give birth. The small holes in the spout give you a gentle spray of water – offering relief from that awful sting if you're recovering from a tear, have stitches or are swollen. We're not going to sugarcoat it: Your vag will be sore, possibly torn, possibly stitched, and peeing will make it feel like it's on fire.  Our Peri Bottle will be a LIFESAVER.

How to Use

Do you use a peri bottle after C section?

The location of your incision makes bending over difficult and mobility limited, so have an Upside Down Peri Bottle to help with cleanup without putting pressure or soreness on the wound site. 

The Upside Down design is practical and includes a narrow neck for a targeted and continuous stream of relief to the intended spot. 

Healing Tip: add our Postpartum Bath Soak to your bottle for even more relief

Pack our portable peri bottle in your hospital bag and use it in that first post birth bathroom trip to make it less scary and easier, as well in the first few days and weeks after giving birth. Included is a carry bag for so it can be discreet.

Also great to use to help clean yourself if you have  haemorrhoids and during menstruation. 

Warnings

Please don't put hot water into the peri bottle and always test the temperature before use.

Warnings

Negative test results do not exclude infection with COVID-19 (so face masks, social distancing and good hygiene practices must be maintained). Negative results should be treated as presumptive only, and do not rule out COVID-19 infection.

Each State and Territory regulates the use of rapid antigen tests. You should ensure your use or consumption of this product adheres to the regulations that govern you. Be aware that there may be penalties for breaching any regulations that apply to you. If you are unsure we recommend that you seek independent legal advice.

previous.name: Nurofen For Children 7+ Pain and Fever Relief Chewable Capsules 100mg Ibuprofen Orange 24 pack
previous.description:
Information

At Nurofen, we know happy kids are playful kids, but sometimes, pain & fever gets in the way. Soft, chewable capsules are great for on-the-go pain relief and can be taken without water. You do the fun and games, we’ll do the headache, pain & fever relief. They provide temporary relief of mild to moderate pains such as: Sore throat Dental pain Ear ache Headache Minor aches Sprains and strains The pain of cold and flu symptoms For the temporary relief of pain and fever. 

Ingredients

Each capsule contains 100mg ibuprofen. Also contains glucose, sucrose and soy lecithin.

How to Use

  • This product should be chewed before swallowing. For oral use.
  • For short term use only.
  • 7 years - 10 years (average weight 22-32kg): Two capsules (max 8 in 24 hours)
  • 10 years - 12 years: (average weight 32-40kg):Three capsules (max 12 in 24 hours)
  • Doses should be given as necessary every 6 to 8 hours (or with a minimum of 6 hours in between each dose if required).
  • Children should take plenty of fluids.

Warnings

  • Do not exceed the stated dose.
  • Excessive use can be harmful and increase the risk of heart attack, stroke and liver damage.
  • Contains sugars and soy lecithin.
Do not use:
  • in anyone with a stomach ulcer, impaired kidney or liver function or heart failure
  • if allergic to ibuprofen or other anti-inflammatory medicines. In case of allergic reaction, stop using and see your doctor immediately during the last months of pregnancy.
Unless a doctor has told you to, do not use:
  • for more than 3 days at a time
  • in children under 7 years of age
  • in children and adolescents suffering from dehydration through diarrhoea and/or vomiting
  • if your child suffers from asthma or chickenpox (varicella)
  • with products containing ibuprofen, aspirin or other anti-inflammatory medicines taken regularly 
  • in adults aged 65 years or over
  • if trying to become pregnant, or during the first 6 months of pregnancy.
  • Do not use if blister foil is broken on first opening.
Always read the label and follow the directions for use.

previous.name: Eagle Tresos Natal 90 Tablets
previous.description:
This product is a Healthcare Practitioner-only dispensed medicine. To allow us to dispatch this product we require you to complete a health questionnaire through the phone to allow our Healthcare practitioner to ensure that this product is suitable for you. Our healthcare practitioner may need to contact you if they feel a further consultation is required based on the product you are purchasing.

Information

  • Helps support optimal nutritional and antioxidant status in mother and baby during pregnancy and lactation.
  • Supports foetal and infant growth and development.
  • Levomefolate calcium (5-Methyltetrahydrofolate/5-MTHF) is the predominant form of folate in the body, it is the most biologically active, acts as a methyl donor, is unlikely to mask Vitamin B12 deficiency and does not result in unmetabolised folic acid in the blood.
  • 5-MTHF is already metabolically active so is directly usable by the body, therefore unaffected by the genetic polymorphism of the enzyme MTHF-reductase and acts as a methyl donor.
  • Calcium folinate (Folinic acid) is a metabolically active form of folate, bypassing the biochemical steps normally required by folic acid.
  • Methylcobalamin is a biologically active form of vitamin B12, functioning as a cofactor to the enzyme methionine synthase, aiding the conversion of homocysteine to methionine.

previous.description:
Information

Anusol suppositories is for the temporary relief of itching, burning and soreness of haemorrhoids and minor rectal inflammations and irritation.

Relieves the pain and discomfort of internal haemorrhoids.

Ingredients

Each suppository contains: Zinc Oxide 300mg (11.0% w/w), Peru Balsam 50mg (1.8% w/w), Benzyl Benzoate 33mg (1.2% w/w).

Also contains Calcium Hydrogen Phosphate, Theobroma Oil, Suppository Base C - Gattefuse

How To Use

This medicine is given via the rectum.

To use suppositories, bathe and dry the affected anal area. Remove from foil and insert one suppository morning and evening and after each bowel movement.

 Lie on your left side with the right knee bent. Carefully push the suppository (pointed side first) just inside the anus with your finger.

Do not push more than an inch or two inside the anus.

Warnings

Always read the label and use only as directed. Seek professional advice if symptoms persist. For external use only. Not to be applied on broken skin.

previous.name: Body Assist Hernia Support Truss 85 - 115cm(S-M)
previous.description:
Information

Inguinal hernia is a rupture to the abdominal wall that causes the intestine to bulge through the opening, under the skin. The pad assist to keep the rupture closed and adds compression to the affected area. It aids recovery, reduces discomfort and maintain your lifestyle with the support you need. Widely used in cases of inguinal, groinal, incisional hernias and femoral Hernia Pain and Discomfort. It is also used for reducible hernias prior and after surgery.

Features & Benefits

  • Applies just the right amount of gentle, gradual pressure to the affected area, while also providing unilateral hernia support for either left or right side.
  • Extra wide flexible waist strap design.
  • Adjustable groin strap can be worn on the left or right to ensure maximum comfort and the perfect compression and tightness level.
  • To move from left to right, simply rotate the waist band around your waist so the pad is positioned over your left or right side groin hernia. Instant relief!
  • Our pressure pad is better than the rest. It has more padding and therefore creates greater pressure against your hernia.
  • It easily adjusts for the perfect compression target, at the perfect location and at the perfect tightness level desired.
  • Hook closures make for easier fitting and adjustment.
  • Contains no metal parts and can be worn while showering and made of lightweight cotton fabrics that give maximum support with day-long comfort.
  • Comfortable quick-drying waistband.
  • Inconspicuous when worn under clothing.
  • Suitable for most activities
  • Completely washable and hygienic.
  • Suits right or left sided hernias.
  • Adjustable Waist Strap.

Medical Data Indications 

  • For men to provide hernia pain relief and help in the treatment process.
  • Cushion applies pressure to the left or right side depending on the location of the hernia.
  • Pad applies gradual pressure and support to weakened muscles of the groin.
  • Recovery.

How to Use

  • Most hernias are one-sided, so you will need to set up the pad on the side that you need it for (left or right). This is very easy to do.
  • 1. Wrap the wider strap around your lower hip and close with pressure (A).
  • 2. Slide the band around the waist so the pad is now over the hernia and secure the leg strap as shown (B).
  • The pad is removable, so move it around till you find your sweet spot.
  • 3. Make final adjustments for maximum comfort and you are done! (C).
  • We advise to wear belt over an undergarment if possible. It just tends to be more comfortable that way.
  • Do not apply over open wounds or if you have a susceptibility to dermatitis.
  • If unsure consult a physician.

Sizing

  • Fully adjustable.
  • Provides constant, comfortable and adjustable pressure to the hernia.
  • Adjustable waistband and leg strap without clunky buckles or snaps.
  • Durable fabric that will not slip, twist or slide.
  • Please note : This product does not have magnets.
  • Suits left or right sided inguinal Hernias.
  • Assists to inhibit skin irritation.
  • Can be worn whilst showering or swimming.

Care

  • Hand wash in warm water.
  • Use mild detergent.
  • Do not bleach.
